# Documentation English Only

All documentation in this project must be written in **English only**. This includes:

## Files that must be in English

- **Markdown documentation files** (`docs/*.md`):
  - `PROJECT_SPEC.md`
  - `BACKLOG.md`
  - `USE_CASES.md`
  - All phase documentation files (`PH*.md`)
  - All test documentation files (`*_TEST*.md`)

- **Changelog** (`CHANGELOG.md`):
  - All version entries
  - All change descriptions
  - All commit messages referenced

- **Cursor rules** (`.cursor/rules/*.mdc`):
  - All rule descriptions
  - All rule content
  - All comments and examples

- **README files** (`README.md`, `archive/README.md`):
  - Project descriptions
  - Setup instructions
  - Usage examples

- **Code comments** (when documenting public APIs or complex logic):
  - Function documentation
  - Class documentation
  - Complex algorithm explanations

## Exceptions

- **User-facing UI text** (Polish is allowed for UI elements visible to end users)
- **Test data** (test fixtures, sample data)
- **Internal code comments** (brief inline comments explaining implementation details)

## Enforcement

When creating or updating any documentation:
1. Write all content in English
2. Use proper English grammar and spelling
3. Follow English documentation conventions
4. If translating existing Polish documentation, ensure accuracy and clarity

## Rationale

- Consistency across the project
- Better collaboration with international developers
- Easier maintenance and updates
- Standard practice for open-source projects
